{
  "stem": "13079.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was that convinced of his guilt.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And let me tell you, when I say convinced of his guilt-- the credibility of the witnesses was the biggest problem that we had.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not that these events didn't occur that the witnesses testified about, but because the nature of the conduct that the witnesses described was so far out-- was so abnormal, with such departures from normal, natural human conduct-- as to be incredible.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When I first heard of it, I didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I thought here were witnesses that were telling me and describing to me events that occurred that couldn't happen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I can give you one that I, I recall.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In each one of these camps there was a place known as the arrest bunker.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the arrest bunker had in it facilities for punishing the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one of them was known as a standing cell.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A standing cell was a device-- and there was more than one-- like a locker in a, a gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was big enough to stand in but you couldn't sit and you couldn't lie down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would take a prisoner and put them in these standing cells and keep them there from three to five days without any food or any water or a chance for them to relieve themselves.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was not at all uncommon that when they would take 'em out of these standing cells, if they were still alive, they would sit-- sit them down at a table on which there had been put a vessel containing about two liters of water.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, the poor prisoner-- starved and almost dying of thirst-- would pick that bottle up and guzzle that water down.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That caused his stomach to expand and stick out.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
